ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W3_CampusMealOrder

Class Name: CampusMealOrder

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 70–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 73 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Create a campus cafeteria order system that handles regular menu items,
limited-stock menu items, successful orders, rejected orders, and a final report.

Program Flow
The main method creates menu items, creates an OrderManager, registers menu items,
processes several order attempts, and prints the final result.

Class Responsibilities
- CampusMealOrderApp: Starts the program and connects objects.
- MenuItem: Represents common menu item data and behavior.
- RegularMenuItem: Represents a normal item without stock limits.
- LimitedMenuItem: Represents an item with stock that decreases after successful orders.
- MealOrder: Represents one successful order.
- OrderManager: Coordinates menu storage, order processing, rejected orders, and reporting.

Requirements
- Use inheritance and polymorphism.
- Store menu items and orders in collections.
- Reject invalid orders safely.
- Update limited stock only after successful orders.
- Print successful orders, rejected orders, total revenue, and remaining stock.